cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper is about image restoration using a multi-path CNN with a pathfinder that selects an appropriate route for each image region. The paper uses reinforcement learning to train the pathfinder, which is related to the fields of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural networks (cs.NE). The focus on image restoration and the use of convolutional neural networks suggest that the paper belongs to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper mentions denoising and mixed restoration tasks, which are related to multimedia (cs.MM).
